article.headline: Kent has 23 in Indiana State's 83-64 win against Valparaiso

images.name: Indiana State's Jayson Kent posterizes defender with mean jam
images.caption: Jayson Kent hangs in the air to throw down a huge dunk for Indiana State.

article.linkText: Kent has 23 in Indiana State's 83-64 win against Valparaiso
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- — Jayson Kent scored 23 points as Indiana State beat Valparaiso 83-64 on Wednesday night. Kent had six rebounds for the Sycamores (23-5, 14-3 Missouri Valley Conference). Xavier Bledson added 15 points while shooting 6 for 8, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc, and he also had six rebounds. Ryan Conwell had 15 points and shot 5 for 11, including 3 for 7 from beyond the arc. The Beacons (6-22, 2-15) were led in scoring by Isaiah Stafford, who finished with 23 points. Jerome Palm added 14 points and two steals for Valparaiso. In addition, Sherman Weatherspoon IV finished with 11 points and two blocks. The Beacons have lost nine straight. Indiana State took the lead with 5:31 remaining in the first half and never looked back. The score was 45-37 at halftime, with Kent racking up 13 points. Kent led the way with a team-high 10 second-half points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
